    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the efficiency thing, but that sounds kinda expensive and complicated for a single person trying to run a shop. it feels like these policies are written by people in cities who dont understand how much harder it is to survive on thin margins in a small town. is there really no valid economic argument for keeping wages lower to prevent businesses from failing?",
